comments.body: In NY no, but I think they tend to be more red in N of range, i.e. in Canada. I recall identifying many from NS with this red color. Of course it wouldn't hurt to check barcode divergences for these...
Could be, not used to seeing so much red on the scutum of luteoloides
Why not N. luteoloides? Wouldn't N. imbricata have less extensively dark propodeum (esp. enclosure)?
